<h5 class="specialH5">Founder's Story</h5>   
    
<div class = "founderstory">
    <img style = "display:block" class = "founderstoryImg" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0587/8674/2454/files/PM_Photo_480x480.jpg?v=1634306630" alt="Nicole Sanchez and Anka Chan" />

    <div style="display:block;font-size: 18px; padding-left: 50px; padding-right: 50px; line-height: 35px;">Nicole and Anka met at the University of Alberta in 2018 when they joined Enactus - a student group focused on social entrepreneurship. They led a project aimed at tackling menstrual waste and launched initiatives to open up conversations surrounding menstruation, sustainable periods, and worked to create sustainable menstrual products from the lab bench. Nearly three years of prototyping and planning led them to launch their company Ruth in January 2021 - an innovative solution to menstrual waste with disposable and biodegradable pads. <br /><br /> Collectively, they have been supported as female founders and trained through Founder Institute, NEXT 36, and the League of Innovators. Ruth is proudly backed by Community Foundations Canada and NEXT Canada.</div>
